name: Zen-East in the Heart of Austin
summary: Zen East is situated in a vibrant & diverse multicultural neighborhood, within walking distance of many great restaurants, cafes, performance/art spaces, UT campus, downtown & just a few miles from a beautiful trail ~ Ladybird Lake. NOTE: As of 1/20/18, new home construction with intermittent noise is happening at lot next door typically b/w hours of 8 - 5:30 pm. Exterior is 90% complete.
space: This colorful and clean 1923 house was completely remodeled in 2004. The house is a 2BR/ 2BA (1350 sq') with a pillow top queen bed in the large master with full private bath and a double futon bed (floor level) in an office which converts to a small guest room adjacent to a full bathroom in the hallway. The following amenities are included: CACH, WIFI, HDTV, washer/dryer, fully equipped kitchen, street parking, fenced back yard with semi privacy fence/deck and front yard with covered porch, pecan, crepe myrtle and other trees provide shade and floral displays in spring.  Whatever is growing in the organic garden, you're welcome to pick and enjoy! Dwellers are culturally diverse and an eclectic blend of artists, professors, students, city employees, long time elderly, retired and business professionals. You will see new home construction as well as old homes in the 'hood.   Please note higher rates during SXSW, Formula One and ACL: $325-$400 per night with minimum 4 night stay for SXSW

notes: A 2013 Genuine Buddy Scooter 125 may be available to rent for $30 a day.  Two  people (~ 300 lbs?) can comfortably ride and helmets (sm & med) will be provided. You must have a motorcycle license and proof of insurance. A small women's bike & helmet may be available for rental as well.
transit: 5 min walk to Capitol Metro Rail (train that takes you downtown) and bus stops within a few minutes (the slowest form of transportation in Austin). B-cycle is a city operated bicycle rental company with several "stations" on the east side where you can rent bikes to get around. You're only 3 miles from Ladybird Lake Trail and bicycling to many parts of central Austin are easy and beautiful along this trail. Uber, Lyft and taxis are in high demand during ACL & SXSW so plan ahead if possible.
access: Several local restaurants, small clubs, music venues, convenience store and cafes within walking distance. Just 1.2 miles from downtown & the University of Texas, ~ 2 miles from the Austin Convention Center & ~ 5 miles from Zilker Park/Barton Springs (ACL location).
interaction: Depending on your dates and arrival time, I am usually available to meet and orient you to the house and answer questions about the neighborhood, restaurants, night life, nature spots, transportation, etc. I'm available via text, phone and email should you have any questions or if an issue arises. I may check in once during your stay. I will always notify you in advance.
house_rules: • Check-in time is 4 pm. Check out is 11 am. I may be able to accommodate earlier check in or later check out so don't hesitate to ask.  Just as you get a glimpse of the house, me & the neighborhood, when contacting me, please provide a brief profile of you and your guests including where you're coming from, the nature of your visit and whatever else you think is helpful. Feel free to ask any questions to help you decide if this is the best place during your stay in Austin.  While guests are welcome to visit, parties and sleep overs are not allowed. You must be on premises while guests are present.  Maximum 4 guests including children. Not childproof.  Sorry, NO PETS, no exceptions, maybe a turtle.  No drugs, heavy drinking, indoor smoking.
host_about:
I am a long time resident of Austin. I earned a few degrees at UT a few decades ago and practice Oriental Medicine, acupuncture, nutrition, herbal medicine & Asian style bodywork. Some of my interests include gardening, meditation, film and film making, dance, tennis, hiking and finding ways to leave a smaller footprint on the planet. 

As your host, I enjoy sharing my home or the “Peapod” (separate dwelling) with visitors from other states and countries as well as with locals. My intention is for your stay to be as comfortable and relaxing as possible. I may check in once or twice by text to see if you have any needs or questions. I have a small dog, Diego, who is sweet & friendly and goes with me when the entire house is rented. 

This host and home are open to people of all colors, faiths and lifestyles. I appreciate guests who are respectful and responsible. 

During the week, the two front rooms of "Zen East" are treatment rooms where I offer Oriental Medicine. One of the rooms is converted into the second bedroom with a double futon (memory foam core) at floor level.  

If you're interested in quality professional massage, acupuncture & or herbal therapy, it may be possible to arrange this "in house". 

Austin offers many fun and unique things to do year 'round.  Some events, like ACL, Formula One and SXSW, leave many folks with few places to stay as hotels tend to book up. You may prefer coming home after a full day to a quiet, home environment, perhaps save a little money cooking some of your meals along with more space, privacy and lounging space.

name: Green, Colorful, Clean &  Cozy home
space: Situated in a vibrant & diverse multicultural neighborhood & within walking distance of many great restaurants, cafes, performance/art spaces, UT campus, downtown & just a few miles from a beautiful trail ~ Ladybird Lake. This green, colorful, clean and cozy house was built in 1923 and remodeled in 2004. As the homeowner, I've taken the liberty to paint each room a different color. The house has plenty of light, shade trees, a fenced back yard and deck, a front porch for sitting with simple landscaping.  Conveniently located in central east Austin, you are: 1 - 2 miles from the University of Texas, Downtown & the Austin Convention Center. You'll find yourself near local cafes and restaurants (Eastside, El Chile, Blue Dahlia, Eastside Pies, Bennu, Salty Sow, Farmacie, Dai Due, Justine's and much more). You're ~ 3 miles from Wheatsville Food Coop, Whole Foods (downtown), Central Market & the Lady Bird Lake trail.   Just a 5 minute walk to Commuter Rail Station will take you downtown duri

notes: Please note: A two story studio has been built in the backyard in early 2017.  You have both a front porch and deck off the bedroom to enjoy the outdoors.
interaction: I should be available, upon your arrival, to answer any questions about the house, Austin, transportation options, restaurants, etc. Other than this, if an interesting conversation happens, fine, but not expected. At any time during your stay, you are welcome to ask/text questions. I may be spending time in the yard/garden, out with friends, walking my dog, spending time on the net or watching TV.  This is your trip and time and I will respect your needs for quiet, privacy, contact and accommodate your needs as best I can. If I am out of town during your stay, you'll be figuring out more on your own but will have the house to enjoy by yourselves.
house_rules: A brief profile for all guests along with photos is requested before your booking is accepted. Helpful info to share: nature of your visit, hours you keep, environment you're looking for. Not allowed: loud parties, smoking (outdoors only), heavy drinking, illegal drugs, pets (small, well behaved may be considered with deposit), fires, including candles, indoors and outdoors.  I expect you to treat this house as if you were visiting your family or a friend and want to be invited back. If you break something, I request that you bring it to my attention as it may not be a big deal. If you don't know how to use an appliance, please contact me.   While guests are welcome to visit during your stay, parties or sleep overs are not permitted.  You must be on the premise when guests are visiting and keys are to be shared with preapproved guests only.  The house is located in a residential neighborhood so respect for neighbors is appreciated. 10 pm noise ordinance applies.  If you have any questi

name: Walk to 6th, Rainey St and Convention Ctr
summary: Fabulous location for walking to Convention Center, Rainey Street, East 6th Street, Downtown, Congress Ave Bats. No additional cleaning fee. Free parking, Free internet City of Austin Hotel Occupancy taxes must be paid upon check-in. No Smoking
space: Cute Private Studio apartment located in Willow Spence National Historic District.  It is  walking distance from Convention Center (3 1/2 blks) and Entertainment District. Save on cab fares.  Bus stop around the corner, takes you straight downtown.   Worried about food?  Great food abounds!  Iron works BBQ 3 blks away,  Cenote and 24 HR IHOP 2 blks away,   Rainey Street with bars and restaurants only 2 1/2 blks away , all within a safe walking distance.  The apartment is located upstairs above garage, completely separate from the main house.  This little 1930's apartment features wood floors and lots of windows.   The kitchen has a full size refrigerator, sink, granite counter-top, microwave, hotpot, toaster oven and coffee-maker. The kitchen does NOT have a  working cooktop, therefore no cooking. neighborhood_overview: My neighborhood is ideally located if you want to walk to bars and restaurants downtown, East 6th Street or Rainey Street.  The Convention Center is only 3 1/2 blocks away and a quick 10 minute walk.
notes: Parking on street requires a permit.  There is a $50 deposit to obtain a permit. 15% hotel taxes must be paid at check-in.  If 6% state occupancy ( Hotel Tax) has been collected by Airbnb, then the remaining 9% City of Austin Occupancy tax must be paid at check-in.  cash , check or online payments accepted.
transit: Bus stop around the block.  Uber, Lyft, Ride, scooters, bikes available.
access: Guests have access to patio.
interaction: I am happy to welcome my guests and show them in.
house_rules: No Pets allowed.  No smoking in the room. No moving furniture.  No Parties.
host_about: I am a licensed Real Estate Broker and owner of Armadillo Realty.  I attended The University of Texas at Austin and fell in love with the small town that it was back in 1979; I have been here every since.  I love the Art, Music and Film scene here in Austin.  There is so much natural beauty to enjoy as well. I especially enjoy Barton Springs Pool in the summertime along with the Zilker Hillside theater productions. SXSW, Austin City Limits Festival and the East Austin Art Studio Tour are among my favorite events. I also enjoy a sunset cruise on my canoe to Congress bridge to see the Mexican Freetail Bats come out for their nightly feeding.

name: NW Austin Room
space: Looking for a comfortable inexpensive room to stay for a night?  A week or more?  Join us in our northwest Austin home where the house is tidy, nicely decorated and we are friendly, responsible, courteous hosts. Single or couples welcome.  I have one small, very shy and quiet dog and we welcome travelers from all over.  You can enjoy your coffee in the morning on the deck with a large backyard, or in the dining area.  Your own Parking spot can be found in front of the house on the granite gravel driveway just beside the mailbox.   The bedroom available in this listing accommodates two persons on a queen bed.   It is next to my study and craft room that sometimes serves as another guest room for a visiting family member or friend but rarely have anyone stay unless I decide to open up this additional space for SXSW, ACL, etc.  This room listing is my primary listing but wanted you to be aware of the 2nd bedroom that may on rare occasions be occupied by another guest. neighborhood_overview: Quiet neighborhood with lots of trees and good neighbors.
transit: We are approximately 16 miles from downtown Austin.  When not traveling during rush hour, I can get to downtown Austin in about 25 minutes but during rush hour, it can take up to an hour.  My location makes it easier for guests with their own mode of transportation but if needed, approximately 2 miles away is the train station which will get you downtown.  The bus is approximately 1.2 miles from the house but sometimes it takes over an hour and a half for the bus to make its way downtown.
access: Gravel Parking Kitchen
interaction: We interact with our guests as little or as much as needed.
house_rules: I will need to see identification at check in. Keys will be provided at that time. Quiet, clean, courteous guests are welcome.  No smoking, candle or incense burning in the house. We love hosting friendly, active guests.  Couch potatoes not so much.  Pets on a case by case basis (small non-refundable deposit required).  Come and go as you please (be courteous regarding noise coming in late at night), LOCK UP AFTER YOURSELF and clean up after yourself in the kitchen, please.  Most importantly, have a great stay!
host_about: We're easygoing professionals that enjoy meeting new people.  I love martial arts, the outdoors, live music, good food and positive people. I can converse in Spanish and can cook a mean Mexican dinner.

name: Gem of a Studio near Downtown
summary: Great studio apartment, perfect for couples or singles. Just 1 mile into downtown. Convenient for walking, biking, Uber or busing into downtown. Airy space with very nice amenities, fresh coffee beans and a private patio. (Yes, we are licensed too!)
space: (License #114332) Large, contemporary studio apartment available for vacation and short-term corporate rental. It's just south of the river and walkable to much of Austin's downtown scene. Our studio apartment sits above the garage and is detached from our main house. It's nicely appointed with plenty of modern amenities. A 37" HDTV with DirecTV Now, Netflix, Amazon, etc., nice cotton sheets, a full kitchen, great private patio with lounge chairs and umbrella, broadband wi-fi, a full bath and shower with its own tankless water heater and more just to name a few features.  We're just south of downtown Austin in the Travis Heights neighborhood. Being just about a mile and half to the Capitol, it's one of the oldest, and being south, it's Austin eclectic. To give you a sense of what's nearby: - About 1 block to the buses going into downtown and less returning (routes 7 and 20) - Across from the Town Lake Hike and Bike Trail, which is up to a 10-mile loop - 1 mile to the convention center

neighborhood_overview: Travis Heights is one of the oldest neighborhoods in Austin. Our house was built in 1937. We rebuilt the apartment in 2009 (well, finished and furnished it for rental then). From the studio it's a pretty easy 1-mile walk through the neighborhood to all the shops and restaurants on South Congress.
notes: Our calendar only extends a few months. If you have interest in future dates, like ACL Fest, please inquire with any dates and we'll sort it out. Thanks.
transit: Parking for our place is on the street, roughly 150 feet from car door to apartment door. The bus stops going to and coming from downtown are within a block. Being so close to downtown, lots of guests simply cross the street and wander into town following the Town Lake Trail. More so in these days of Uber and Lyft, our guests are opting to not get a rental car and just get rides as needed around downtown.
access: Private patio with lounge chairs and umbrella.
interaction: You may see us during your stay, but you'll maintain your privacy because the apartment is a separate building. Sometimes we only see our guests upon check-in. Sometimes not at all!
house_rules: Posted prices include the 9% in local occupancy taxes required of all Austin rentals. As of 5/1/17, Airbnb will start collecting the 6% state taxes. We keep a copy of our City of Austin-granted Operating License in the apartment. Non-smoking home. Smoking is only allowed outside on the back patio. Pets are not permitted. There's never been a pet in the apartment.  Minimum stay is 2-3 nights depending on the season. Some special events and holidays have longer minimum stays and higher minimum rates.
host_about:
We're a young family that likes to travel, we just don't get to enough. So we live vicariously through our visiting guests. 

We run this little vacation rental apartment ourselves. As mentioned in the listing, it's located on our property. It's an above garage apartment that is completely separate from our home. We like to think it's a bit European to share our place with guests. We're very sensitive to guests' needs and give you plenty of space. We're happy to answer any questions about Austin, help you around town, make suggestions, and more if you'd like. We've lived in Austin for more than 15 years and have been renting the studio for more than seven years and make improvements as we grow with it. Thank you for considering our place.

PS. No, our profile pic was not taken in Austin:)

name: Secluded Studio in 78704 (Zilker)
summary: Our garage apartment provides a private space with everything you need for a quiet, comfortable stay close to downtown Austin. Quality furnishings and amenities will make you feel like you're staying at home rather than in a rental or hotel. **Please be aware of the CoA tax that we will collect at checkin (see below)**
space: Stay in our lovely 1 bedroom garage apartment and enjoy the quiet of our 78704 'hood while being close-in for all the fun! Walking distance to downtown, hop on a 7-min Capital Metro bus (rte 29), or take a $5 cab/Uber ride in. Also, 5-10 min walk to restaurants (Chuy's, Shady Grove, Austin Java, Shake Shack, Uchi), Alamo Drafthouse, and Barton Springs Bike Rental. Want more? Zilker Park, Barton Springs Pool, Barton Creek Greenbelt, Hike and Bike Trail, and other outdoor entertainment all within one mile.  The apartment:  One bedroom with queen bed, bath, kitchenette, WiFi/Internet access (no cable TV, sorry). Pull-out memory-foam couch also available (and/or inflatable mattress).  32" flat screen TV.  Kitchenette has full size stove/oven, mini refrigerator, coffee maker, toaster, blender, and microwave. It is also stocked with coffee, tea, creamer, and sweeteners. neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is fun and funky (but quiet)! People are friendly  and you can't beat the location.
notes: You may hear the garage door go up on weekday mornings around 6:30a when we have to bring the kids to school. However, we are very mindful of using the garage when we have guests upstairs. And we like to leave the outside light on over night. You can turn it off if it bothers you, though. Finally, PLEASE NOTE that the prices listed DO NOT include the legally required 9% City hotel tax (AirBNB collects the State hotel tax). Guest is responsible for paying this AT CHECK IN. Tax payment can be left in the taxes envelope on the microwave. They are 9% of your rental amount. There will be an invoice left for you. Thanks for your understanding.
transit: There's a bus route just outside the 'hood plus you can easily walk into downtown, catch a cab, call a ride share, or use a smart car.
access: We will either meet you and show you in or we can arrange to leave the apt open for you. The key pad code is 8080.
interaction: We'll interact as much as you like. We respect our guests' privacy but really enjoy hosting. We are here 99% of the time but follow our guests' lead on interaction.
house_rules: * No parties. * No smoking in the apartment. If you smoke on the balcony, please use an ashtray and empty your ashes/butts in the trash behind the garage (on the alley). * No candles or incense. * When you leave to go out for the day (everyday), please turn the AC/heat off or up so that's it's not running all day. * Golden rule: Leave the place as you found it. Finally, PLEASE NOTE that the prices listed DO NOT include the legally required 9% City hotel tax (AirBNB collects the State hotel tax). Guest is responsible for paying this AT CHECK IN. Tax payment can be left in the taxes envelope on the microwave. They are 9% of your rental amount. There will be an invoice left for you. Thanks for your understanding.
host_about: We are a family of four (with small kids). We love our home town and location... can't beat the park, river, and downtown. We love having guests in our garage apartment... it's fun to talk to people about their lives, hometowns, and travels. We're happy to give recommendations and want you to be comfy.

name: Woodland Studio Lodging
space: Fully furnished suite with kitchen, bathroom, breakfast counter, sitting area with sofa, and queen-sized bed.  Private patio entrance opens out onto large yard.  Stay close to downtown, SoCo, and artsy East Austin. This quiet neighborhood just off of Woodland Avenue has beautiful old oak trees, so it stays pleasant and shady through the summer.  Nearby city bus routes, so it is easy and inexpensive to get around, even if you don't have a car.  (Avoid the hassles of parking, too!)  Or rent a bike instead of a car.  Within easy reach of the airport. Stays of 2 weeks or more are $50/night.  Please ask and we can send a special offer with the reduced pricing.   Higher rates may apply during holidays, special events, depending on length of your stay. Please note, although there is a wireless internet connection, there is not a tv in the studio. Austin Short Term Rental License #085368

name: 30's Cottage, Trav Hghts, SoCo, almost dwntwn
summary: A Travis Heights  jewel, on a quiet (no-outlet) street in elegant Old Austin. Walk 5 blks to So Congress full of restaurants, eclectic shops & street vendors--Jo's Coffee (Sunday band), Amy's icecream, Continental Club, Home Slice Pizza. Watch the bats fly on Congress Bridge. Take an Uber downtown (5 min) to 2nd, 4th and 6th Streets for night life & music. House borders Stacy Park hiking trails, playground & pool. Live in the heartbeat of what makes Austin cherished by so many...& a little weird
space: Sleeps 5; 2 BR, 2 Bath. The upstairs Treehouse Bedroom and Bath has a sitting area and queen tempurpedic bed; The downstairs Patio bedroom and Bath has a queen bed and extra single bed (upon request); it opens to a private sitting patio through double french doors. The sunny Living room has a comfortable twin futon bed/ couch.  Please note Pet Fee of $40 (enclosed patio).  The historic Travis Heights home is beautifully decorated and landscaped, modern everything, central air/heat, full size washer/dryer, shaded and gated patio and plenty of off-street parking, large pecan trees, lots of light and charm.  Next to a walk bridge across the Blunn Creek and you are in Stacy park, 1 mile long with a 30 meter swimming pool. Walk to the Congress Ave Bridge to watch the bats fly and visit Downtown's famous 6th, 4th, and now 2nd Street districts for live music and night life. The home nestled under towering Pecan and Live Oak trees is ‘Old Austin' at its finest. Experience its grace, romance an

neighborhood_overview: South Austin is eclectic mix, known for funky creativity, street musicians and friendliness. Though somewhat gentrified as Austin has grown, this central, almost downtown neighborhood is cherished for being down-home, helpful and appreciative of diversity.  Congress avenue is a stream of people watching; while so close, it does not impact our the quiet neighborhood.
notes: The neighborhood is safe, established and mature.  We appreciate guests who keep a quiet and respectful presence.  No parties. Groove on the squirrels and neighbors walking with dogs and babies on their way to Stacy Park. I have one bike, in good shape, and two tennis rackets.
transit: Walk 5 block through lovely homes, towering trees and quiet streets to Congress Avenue. On Congress you'll find dozens of fine dining and casual restaurants, bars, and great (weird) shopping--all within a few walking blocks of my house. You don't need a car. On Congress take Uber ($7) or catch many buses to downtown and other parts of Austin (and avoid downtown parking).
access: Complete home, 2 levels.  Handicap assessable.
interaction: I'm available by cellphone and text during all of your stay.
house_rules: Quiet after 10 pm.   No parties. Pets must be pre-approved and are subject to an additional $40 fee. Leave the home in the same clean condition you found it, minus laundry.
host_about: I love living in the heart of what people cherish about Austin--the activity, shops, and restaurants on South Congress, the Hike & Bike trail along Town Lake, and the downtown live music scene on 2nd, 4th and 6th Streets (just a 5 min Uber ride away.)  I enjoy my profession as a relationship counselor specializing in intimate communication and touch, so I get to help Keep Austin Sexy!

neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood is a mix of students and single family houses, so it is very eclectic. There are plenty of restaurants and shops to walk to nearby and we're within minutes of almost everything else.
notes: This is a non-smoking property.  It is absolutely prohibited indoors and in the outdoor spaces as well. We charge you for leaving butts on the property or for lingering odors inside.   We are located near campus, so you often can hear music nearby, though we've never had any complaints about neighborhood noise being heard inside the house. The lot is large and quiet, even though we're right in the middle of town.
transit: We have private off-street parking on the property for guests with cars.  We are located within a block or two of public transportation that can get you downtown within minutes.  Guests staying a week or more can request complimentary bus passes. There are other options available in Austin such as Lyft, Uber, Car2Go, Zipcar, and standard taxi services. We can provide more information and links for any of these services.
access: In addition to the house, guests have access to the driveway, carport, and yards.  The patio, grill, pool, and heated spa are also available to guests.
interaction: Hosts do not live on the property, but are nearby and can respond to needs typically within minutes.  We have an information binder in the house with recommendations and answers to the main questions we've received over the years.
house_rules: * Signed rental agreement may be required. A digital copy can be provided upon request. * Must be 25 years or older to rent. * NO SMOKING ANYWHERE ON THE PROPERTY. We do not rent to smokers. A monetary penalty will be applied if any evidence of smoking (butts, odors, burn marks, etc.) is found after your stay. * There is a limit of 6 total overnight guests.  * Pets and kids over 5 years of age are welcome at no extra charge, but you must declare them and you must pick up after them. * The availability of the pool is not guaranteed. Algae blooms, repairs, and other unforeseen occurrences may make the pool unusable. We will not give discounts or refunds if the pool is unavailable. * Guests of guests: Our property is not available for pool parties or gatherings of more than 10 people. All of the same rules apply to guests of guests. No guests of guests under the age of 5, especially in the pool, and all guests of guests must pick up after their pets as well. Guests of guests may not smoke
host_about: We were born and raised here in Austin and have grown and changed right along with this funky town.  We have owned rental property in Austin for 30+ years.  We used to have long-term rentals and switched to short-term in 2007 when there were only 60 other vacation rentals in town. We've loved it so much that we have branched out into other states as well.  We tend to leave you alone during your stay, but we're close by if you need anything!

name: Clarksville Condo - Minutes to DT!
summary: This is one of the funnest, most walkable neighborhood in all of Austin.  You can Uber/RideShare to downtown for $5.00.  Friendly people, beautiful houses and lots to see, do, eat and drink.  Come see why this is such a great area!
space: What a fabulous location! Thinking about moving to Austin? Renovating your home? Coming for work? Clarksville is minutes from downtown and so close to everything you want to see and do. See the fabulous Whole Foods, have a burger and a shake at Nau's, enjoy a margarita at sundown at Z' Tejas or go to a gallery on 6th Street. Clarksville has a dry cleaners, grocery store, restaurants, salons, shops, Cafe Medici, a wonderful park, playground and wading pool, convenience store, galleries and so much more.  Condo is fully equipped with pots, pans, furniture, linens, towels washer & dryer inside unit.  Bed is queen-sized.  Pack your bags and come to Austin! host_about:
I'm a dog lover, music lover, good friend, happy person (but not one of those annoying happy people - you know what I'm talking about), and I enjoy meeting new people.  Apparently, I'm also a walking cliche...metaphor...hyperbole, whatever.
I do a lot of traveling and make it a point to stay in vacation rentals as often as I can.  Since I love it so much, I thought I'd share my house with people passing through Austin - after all, it IS the coolest city on the planet...well, in the US, anyway.  
Hope you'll visit!

interaction: We will be present and are happy to interact with guests as much or as little as they like.  The apartment is attached to our home where we live and work. Therefore we are close by in the event you need/want us. We try to provide the amount of interaction our guests desire.

One shower which we share.  I will provide a few toiletries to start.  I have bath towels and sheets you can use but feel free to bring your own if you prefer.  Room is cool in summer and war
neighborhood_overview: It is a quiet street with few kids.  The surrounding kids are usually in by 8pm.   Most kids are in by  8pm.  It is quiet even on weekends.  Because I am single, I do have an alarm system and security cameras.
notes: No overnight guests.  You can have visitors with permission but room is only for one person. There is no room for storing anything in the house or my garage.
transit: There are two bus stops at each end of street that can take you downtown and back.  The fast MetroRail is in the Domain shopping center location 5 min. away. If I am available and its not during traffic hours, I can pick you up or take you to airport for $20.00. Advance notice is needed.
access: You have access to your room, bathroom,  shower, washer and dryer in garage, and the kitchen.   You will have access to the full kitchen, stove, refrigerator, utensils, dishes, cooking pans, and coffee maker.  There is a washer and dryer in garage and wireless Internetin the house.  There is a TV in your room for local television.  Big screen TV in living room to watch Netflix or Amazon movies is available.  There is no storage for things in my garage.  All things must fit in your room. Please only bring laptop or computer, clothes, toiletries, etc.  No furniture. Room is fully furnished.  If you have a bike, bring a cover for it.  There is room in the backyard for it but it won't be covered.
interaction: I have lived in Austin for over 13 yrs. so I can fill you in on activities in the city, ways to meet people, etc. I belong to many social and business networking groups.
house_rules: Please take shoes off if muddy.  I unfortunately still have carpet throughout and maintain it regularly with shampooings.  No loud noise after 11pm.  No company in the house while I am not home or arrangements have been made. I keep house tidy so all I ask is that you clean up after yourself, and put dirty dishes in dishwasher. I will maintain the rest.
host_about: Single female with 2 well-behaved Yorkies who do not shed are clean, and well-behaved. Live in a nice, very clean, quaint home that is feng shui-ed for harmony as this is my business.  I mentor in Big sister program.  Non-smoker.  Love to travel to explore new places and have new experiences.  Am a world traveler.  While you are in my home, I am social but will respect your privacy.

summary: Large and airy, 380 square foot, studio space in Southeast Austin! 5 miles from airport, McKinney Falls State Park, and downtown Austin; 10 miles from Circuit of the Americas/F1 track; 15 minutes walking to Onnit Academy; public bus stop across the street with bus every 15 minutes...musician friendly!! Please keep in mind this is a residence, not a hotel, and guests are responsible for reading ALL info and arriving prepared for self checkin on occasion.
space: Beautiful studio space available in Austin! Amenities include: parking; private entrance; FREE washer and dryer; full PRIVATE bathroom with shower and towels; kitchenette with hot plate, toaster oven, electric kettle, and mini-fridge; one DOUBLE sized, tempurpedic platform bed with amazing memory foam topped mattress; queen air mattress for additional guests; wi-fi; sprung wood floors; front garden for chillin'.  Since this room functions as my music room when it's not being rented, it is almost soundproof. Musicians looking for a place to stay where they can practice without worry are welcomed and encouraged to stay here!!  Around the corner from the #7 bus route which can take you almost ANYWHERE in Austin, including 6th street and Warehouse districts; University of Texas, Austin; and all the way to Highland Mall in North Austin (use the CapMetro site for schedules and planning). neighborhood_overview: This is "real" south Austin...don't be surprised to hear Tejano, and even Mariachis, on a Friday or Saturday night...excellent taco truck around the corner for breakfast and lunch, or until they run out of tortillas, with bus stop located there.
notes: The neighbors have some urban, free range, chickens and roosters...if you're a super light sleeper, bring ear plugs, but with the a/c or fan running, most guests tell me they don't hear them :)
transit: Super easy and inexpensive public bus (#7 runs from William Cannon in the south, all the way through downtown, the Capitol, UT campus, and end of line at Highland Mall) available to get around...pickup to downtown around the corner on Teri Lane in front of the mini mart, and drops across the street on Teri as well). Lyft from airport $15; Lyft to downtown $13; Lyft to SoCo district $8-10
access: Studio is private and independent in-law style apartment attached to my main residence.
interaction: I'm frequently available to guests to answer questions and offer recommendations, and sometimes even invite them out for an evening of music or dancing with me! However, you have your own entrance, so if you prefer total privacy, you can have that, too!
house_rules: Please park your car directly in front of the studio entrance (double wide stained glass doors, right hand parking space as you face the doors).  If you have prepared food, please wash up your dishes with the detergent and sponge provided in the rest room. We provide you with a clean space on arrival, but not maid service during your stay.  You are responsible for emptying your own garbage and recycling if needed (garbage and recycling bins are located just outside the studio doors on the side of the house; Austin practices "single-stream recycling," so please just put all paper, cardboard, plastics, and glass in the large blue bin--gray is for trash). Laundry detergent and bleach are located on top of the washer, as is extra soap, shampoo, conditioner, and toilet paper! Please help yourself. Wifi router is located on the shelf above the dryer in the laundry room if you need to reset it for any reason, and the breaker box for the studio AND house is to the left of the laundry room door
host_about: I'm a full time professional musician, and founder and teaching artist of the Roots & Rhythms Cultural Arts Program, currently working with at-risk youth thanks to a grant from the city of Austin's Cultural Contracts division and the National Endowment for the Arts. I love playing host to travelers and concert goers.

host_about: After 8 years living in New York City, I relocated to my home state of Texas, settling in the vibrate downtown Austin community of Clarkesville in 2007.   I enjoy entertaining - love eating outdoors, cooking - my signature offering is French bread and jalapeno jelly, eating - anything and everything!, sampling wines and beers from all over the world and enjoying the great outdoors.  My sentiment about travel is 1) getting there really can be half of the fun and 2) go local!  Local grocery stores and markets can really convey the sensibilities of any locale.  My goal is to accomodate my guests' interests and how they want to experience Austin but I do have a "local" bias.  I look forward to hosting you in my guest house.

name: Colorful and Quirky Zilker Park Townhouse
summary: Kick back at this multicolored two-story townhouse jam-packed with original art and loaded with all the modern amenities. Wake up in a comfy bed and head just around the corner to Zilker park for a morning jog, then cook a meal in the fully-equipped kitchen.
space: ***IMPORTANT: ONE NIGHT STAYS ARE AVAILABLE ON WEEKDAYS ONLY. YOU MUST BOOK A MINIMUM OF 2 NIGHTS ON THE WEEKENDS UNLESS THERE IS ONLY ONE NIGHT AVAILABLE.  Monthly and weekly prices available at non special event times.  Please ask for pricing.  *One of the coolest places in Austin. Feels good. Looks good. Art and  color every where.  *Exceptional Garden. Best one in the neighborhood. *Quiet two story townhome that is part of a four-plex on a very quiet street.  * One comfy King bed upstairs with a full bath. * Half bath downstairs and fold out queen (with memory foam found in downstairs closet) *Fish Tank Toilet *Washer/Dryer *Kitchen set up for gourmet cooking *Patio with grill *Stay for a night or for several months *All photos in space taken by me
description: Kick back at this multicolored two-story townhouse jam-packed with original art and loaded with all the modern amenities. Wake up in a comfy bed and head just around the corner to Zilker park for a morning jog, then cook a meal in the fully-equipped kitchen.
neighborhood_overview: Located on a quiet street in 78704, which is one of the city's best neighborhoods. It's a short walk to Barton Springs pool, the botanical gardens, and Zilker Park. An abundance of food trucks, restaurants, and bike rentals is less than a mile away.
notes: There is a book on the coffee table with everything you will need to know about the space.  You will also find an entire book of restaurant suggestions and other info.
transit: I always recommend a car but there are certainly other options.  Please feel free to ask, here are some local resources: BICYCLE RENTAL bartonspringsbikerental spinster CAR RENTALS carrental---info about airport car rental Enterprise Austin Car2Go – (Often seen parked in the neighborhood.) With free parking around Austin, you only have to pay for the time you are actually driving the car. (.41/minute)  You will need to go online, join, and get your Car2Go ID card to use the system. NO monthly fees.  Public Transportation (URL HIDDEN) Go Line: Call for info on all buses One Way Pass $1.25 Day Pass $2.50 Local Cab Companies Yellow Cab Fasten and Fare are local ride share Uber and Lyft no longer available
access: You can arrive any time you like 4 PM or later.  There is a lock box on the front door with the key inside. Once you book, you will be sent the code in the itinerary that you will receive from airbnb.
interaction: I always try to meet my guests during their stay (if I am in town).  Call any time and hopefully we will meet upon arrival. If possible please let me know what time you think you might be arriving.
house_rules: There are neighbors so nice quiet peaceful guests are always appreciated.  No smoking inside.  Please read all details before instant booking or ask questions.
host_about: Professional Intuitive and relationship advice columnist.. Lived here since 1981. I know my way around Austin and don't mind telling you all about it. Art car artist since 1999. I have decorated 5 cars and you will probably see my car in the driveway when you arrive. Weird home owner. Doing my best to keep Austin weird.

space: You will never forget your stay in this luxuriously appointed, utterly charming and vintage "jewel box" of a house in the Zilker Park neighborhood. The charm of our Zilker Cottage is exceeded only by its perfect location.  This is an original vintage (approximately 650 square feet) 1940's Zilker Cottage in the very BEST location within 1/2 mile from DOWNTOWN AUSTIN with a cozy bedroom, bathroom, living room, dining room, huge kitchen, and vine covered front porch.  Street parking is available (for free) directly in front of the house about 25 feet from the front door.  You can look forward to staying so close to downtown but in a safe, upscale, and cool Zilker residence.  Best of both worlds. name: Live Beneath Live Oaks in a Bright, Intimate House
summary: Curl up with a book on the comfy window seat of this stand-alone studio loft. The vibrant open-plan space features a yellow bistro table, a red-lacquer kitchenette, and a cozy sleeping nook. Relax on either of two patios beneath live oaks.
space: Welcome to the "Birdhouse" a beautiful, quiet, light-filled studio located under large Live Oak trees in our backyard.  Enjoy the weather with two outdoor areas: a shady limestone patio with comfortable seating and a sunny gravel patio. Inside the open-plan first floor is 350 square feet (32.5 square meters) and includes: A bed nook with a very comfortable natural queen mattress bed outfitted with clean crisp sheeting. A fully stocked kitchenette, with two burner gas cook top, under-counter fridge, convection microwave, and all the cooking supplies needed to make everything from a great cup of coffee in the morning to a cozy dinner.   A well appointed bathroom with over-sized shower (supplied with endless hot water thanks to the tank-less water heater), fluffy towels, and hairdryer.    A lovely seating area with a cozy window seat.  Off street parking, for one car; High speed Wifi; and iPod dock are also provided. We are located approximately 2 miles south of downtown in-between South
description: Curl up with a book on the comfy window seat of this stand-alone studio loft. The vibrant open-plan space features a yellow bistro table, a red-lacquer kitchenette, and a cozy sleeping nook. Relax on either of two patios beneath live oaks.
neighborhood_overview: Located in the cool Dawson area, about two miles south of downtown, the house is a short walk to coffee shops, a rock-climbing gym, and a variety of eateries. Public transportation is nearby.
notes: Use loft/ladder at your own risk. Please use caution and common sense on the loft ladder. No children under 12 in the loft. If you have been drinking, or are otherwise physically compromised, please do not use the ladder/loft.  The loft is not a sleeping space.
transit: We are located within a short walk of restaurants, coffee shops, and shopping.  The bus stop is a 4 minute walk away, which will take you downtown and beyond with no transfers.  The bus downtown takes around 15 minutes or you can drive to downtown in 5-7 minutes.  All of central Austin in within close driving distance of the house.  The airport is a short 15 minute drive.
interaction: The casita is in our backyard, so we will be around if you need anything or just want to chat. If not, the casita is all yours so feel free to revel in your alone time.
house_rules: We live in the house in front of the casita and so we expect reciprocal respect.  Please let us know if you need anything! Also, please notify us if something breaks or is not in working order. We will work to correct any problems as quickly as possible.  No smoking (including e-cigarettes/vaping) in the house, and if you must smoke please do so on the back patio (dispose of your butts in the metal trashcan, not in the house trash).  Use loft/ladder at your own risk. Please use caution and common sense on the loft ladder. No children under 12 in the loft. If you have been drinking, or are otherwise physically compromised, please do not use the ladder/loft. The loft is not a sleeping space. Finally, per the Airbnb Host Guarantee Terms and Conditions  (http://www.airbnb.com/terms ) please be aware that you will be liable for all loss and damages incurred during your stay. By booking a reservation you agree to pay for any damage you do to the property.  Thanks!
host_about: My husband and I spent a year traveling the world in 2008. We stayed in literally hundreds of places. Some were great and some were awful, but what the great ones all had in common was a welcoming host that helped us feel more like locals. Airbnb gives us the opportunity to welcome other travelers to our part of the world.

name: South 1st Garage Apartment - Ideally Central
summary: New Construction (June '17) centrally located off of S. First, close to S. Congress, S. Lamar, and all that downtown has to offer.  You'll love the modern design, natural light, 14' ceilings, high-end finishes, and the neighborhood. A 550 sf apartment with bedroom, living area with pull out sofa bed (brand new, very comfortable), small dining table, desk area, balcony, a screened in reading porch, WiFi, Apple TV, and local TV.  Ideal for an Austin adventure or a quiet, productive work trip.
space: Contemporary apartment extremely well appointed.  Kitchen has all brand new Bosch appliances including a speed oven, gas range with exhaust vent-a-hood, full-sized refrigerator and freezer, and Caesar-stone counter tops.   Coffee maker and coffee is provided with Austin-based coffee bean brand.  The bathroom features a walk-in shower with Speakman fixtures and a large rain shower head and contemporary tile and finishes. There are wood floors throughout with vaulted ceilings above and furnished with brand-new West Elm furniture and brand-new Pottery Barn bedding.  The sleeper sofa is the West Elm Henry Deluxe Queen size that is designed without uncomfortable bars or springs, it pulls open easily to reveal a plush-top mattress - so comfortable  it feels like a real bed. Interesting lighting sets the mood whether working in the open Desk nook or lounging in bed.   Full size washer and dryer are concealed within the built-in closet that also includes a chest-of-drawers and hanging rods.

neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood is in central Austin off of vibrant South First.  We are in a quiet neighborhood between South Congress and South Lamar and less than 2 miles from downtown, Auditorium Shores, Lady Bird Lake and the Lady Bird Lake running and biking trail, and Austin bike share stations.  You can take a  two mile run through the neighborhood to the decomposed granite running and biking trail around Lady Bird Lake. summary: Located in French Place neighborhood near campus and very central. Behind my house is a separate guest cottage, 1 bdrm, 1 bath cottage that has its own entrance and complete privacy.

summary: I do not book more then 4-6 weeks in advance.  Therefore please, DO NOT REQUEST more than 4-6 weeks in advance. THIS INCLUDES SPECIAL EVENTS - SXSW, ACL, etc... Also discuss all pets with me prior to booking.
space: This is a for a 1 bedroom- 1 bath  apartment above (what used to be) the garage and is now the Studio at SOCO.  We are located one block off of Congress.    Located in 78704, this is very close to Hotel San Jose and Kimber Modern and Saint Cecilia. We have currently have this configured  as two twins but with 30 minutes notice I can change it back to a King Size bed. Kitchen, great Sitting area with couch that opens to a bed and large table with six chairs. Generally used as an office, we have it for guests or special events.  South Congress is full of restaurants to walk to including  Perla's and Hopdoddy. We are a 4 block walk to Home Slice and Hey Cupcake. You may not need to rent a car.  There is a city bus that runs along South Congress and drops you off downtown.   There are lots of car2gos in the neighborhood.  We have 2 Bikes you can rent/borrow. host_about:
Stephanie and Michael wanted to live in walking distance of something.   We love our house and its location. From here we can walk to restaurants and coffee shops and all the rest of Austin comes to South Congress. 

Our house is a great mix of a 1935 Craftsman  and a modern infusion of steel and concrete.   The two places we list on this site are the upstairs and downstairs of the former garage. 
 
Stephanie works in animal welfare and real estate and Michael is a Clean Energy Executive. mdbreen is his id on most social media sites.

She travels as much as I do and we love co-creating these experiences on airbnb together.

name: Architect Designed - Great Location
summary: Our architect designed, modern home comfortably sleeps up to four people. Gourmet kitchen, natural light, full backyard with grill. Located in the hip SOCO neighborhood, walking distance to several excellent restaurants and boutique shopping.
space: Beautiful Architect designed two-story, modern home built in 2006, featured in the 2006 Austin AIA Homes Tour, hardwood floors, 2 bedrooms, 2 full tiled baths, gourmet kitchen which opens to the living area and dining area, lots of windows and natural light, house sits under a towering Live Oak tree.  The home comfortably sleeps up to four adults.  Upstairs: one queen bed and full bath, and washer/dryer.  Downstairs: a double bed and full bath.  The dining area has place settings for up to eight people.  The living area includes a 42" mounted plasma television.  Entertainment: TV (Basic Cable), DVD, and wireless internet.  Clean towels and linens provided.  The backyard deck has a gas grill, great for BBQ, a chair swing hung under the Live Oak, and deck furniture for outdoor dining or relaxation.  Street parking is available out front and not a problem.  Taxes: a 15% tax rate is included in the nightly rate. The property is registered with the City of Austin as a short-term rental. STR

neighborhood_overview: The home is conveniently situated in Austin's centrally located and hip South Congress (SoCo) neighborhood. The house is located on a quiet street one block from South Congress Avenue and 3 blocks from S. 1st Street. Walking distance to local bars/clubs, restaurants, and boutiques including the Continental Club (a SXSW venue), Jo’s Coffee, Hotel San Jose, Guero’s, Perla's, Home Slice Pizza, Amy’s Ice Cream, Hop Doddy Burgers, Vespaio/Enoteca, South Congress Cafe, Wahoo Tacos, Magnolia Cafe, Bouldin Creek Coffee, El Chile, Polvo's, Elizabeth Street Cafe, La Patisserie, Sway, Sugar Mama's Cupcakes, Dolce Neve Gelato, Freddy's, and Allen’s Boots and several boutiques.   HEB Grocery is 4 blocks and Farm to Market Grocery 2 blocks for provisions.  .  Lady Bird Lake, 5 min drive or 40 min walk for walking, running, and biking trails.  Little Stacy Park/Playground/Public tennis court is 15 minute walk. Stacy public pool for swimming year-round is a 10 minute walk.
notes: Cleaning Fee of $100 Security deposit fee of $650 Once you book a one page "Rental Agreement" will be emailed to you as well as a request for a copy of your passport/driver's license of the person financially responsible for the owner to have on file.
transit: The heart of Downtown (6th and Congress) is 2.2 miles or a 40 minute walk, 5 min cab ride or 11 minute bus ride.  University of Texas is 3.5 miles.  Local bus (CapMetro) service is less than one block from the house and a quick trip to most SXSW venues (note: cabs will be needed for late night).  Airport is a 12-15 minute drive w/o traffic.  Parking is available in front of the house, on-street parking.
access: The entire house and backyard. We leave the pantry stocked and just ask that guests replace any cooking item that is used up.  The garage is not available.
interaction: We like to meet our guests when they arrive to hand over the keys. Otherwise we are a phone call away if any questions or problems.  This is our private home but we go elsewhere when rented out.
house_rules: Please treat our home as you would yours.  We live on a quiet street with several families. Quiet after hours is appreciated.   No additional guests allowed unless approved by the owner. No commercial use unless approved by the owner.  No pets please. No smoking please.
host_about: Married couple in their 40s. Steven grew up in Austin and Becca in Philadelphia. Our house was designed by Steven's best friend from growing up and has been on several architectural tours. We love to travel and explore new places and would love to share our home for folks to explore Austin.

summary: Located in the heart of one of Austin's hottest neighborhoods - walking distance to S. Lamar, S. 1st & S. Congress! A mile and a half from downtown, Zilker Park, and Ladybird Lake.  Great 2 bedroom with open concept living; sleeps up to 6. Money Magazine has listed S. 1st as one of the top 10 hippest neighborhoods in the country.  (Website hidden by Airbnb)
space: Enjoy one of Austin's coolest neighborhoods! This comfortable 2BR/1BA house is located just south of downtown Austin and minutes from Zilker Park. The house is walkable to the popular South Congress (SoCo), South First street, and South Lamar. The living room couch pulls out into a full-size bed for additional guests.  Cookware is provided. There is a TV with a Roku system. Roku allows you to sign into your video streaming accounts, such as Netflix, Hulu, Amazon, and HBO Go. There is an antennae for basic/local channels and wireless internet. The front porch offers a great spot for relaxing and enjoying the neighborhood vibe, and there is a table in the backyard as well. There is a 2- car driveway for off-street parking, and a full-size washer & dryer. Three night stays are required for weekends and special events such as ACL, SXSW, F1), but two-night stays will be considered for an additional $50 fee. *You must inquire with me first before booking over festivals and holidays to ensure

neighborhood_overview: Walking to breakfast or lunch at neighborhood cafes and fine dining restaurants, hopping on the City bus one block away, walking to the neighborhood park one block away, a twenty minute walk from Auditorium Shores and Ladybird Lake, a quick bike ride to Zilker Park,  staying in the same neighborhood as residents movie star Elijah Wood and musician Robert Plant!
transit: The most popular form of transportation is Fasten or  GetMe. Similar to a taxi service, but typically less expensive. Download the app to your phone and see how affordable it is! Austin’s bus system, Capitol Metro, costs only $1 per single ride or $2 for an all-­day pass. The number 5 (Woodrow/S 5th bus) picks up one block away at the corner of S. 5th and Mary and goes directly into downtown (a 10 minute ride). There are also routes that pick up on Lamar. Numerous other connections pick-­‐up at various locations throughout downtown. Bike rentals are available! We've partnered with a local shop to provide our guests with the option to rent bicycles during their stay (for an additional fee). Please advise us if you're interested in this service so we can help get you set up for bike delivery/pick-up.
access: You can check-in at any time after 3 PM. The home features keyless entry, you will receive a code to the electronic locks approximately 1 week before your arrival so you can comfortably check in anytime.
interaction: Natalia is available via phone call, text and e-mail if you have any questions or issues before/during/after your stay. Myself and my property manager, Natalia, work very hard to respond timely and quickly to your inquiries or any needs during your stay. We sincerely love hosting our guests and strive to make your visit a pleasant one. We will do what we can to make sure you are taken care of while staying in my home.
house_rules: PLEASE READ, this is required prior to booking. - If you have a pet, do not utilize instant book. Pets must be approved prior to booking and with applicable pet fee paid ($25 per pet, per night). Pets MUST be housetrained and stay off furniture/bedding, otherwise additional fees will be withdrawn from security deposit. Pet waste must be picked up from the yards and any other area, otherwise additional fees will be withdrawn from security deposit. - If you have more than 4 guests, please ensure you have noted the correct number of guests prior to booking to ensure all fees are paid. - No parties are allowed. There are a number of bars/restaurants close by that stay open late – please utilize them -Smoking is not allowed in the house. An ashtray can be found on the front porch. Please leave all cigarette butts in the ashtray (not in the yard!). A withdraw will be taken from the security deposit if cigarette smoke is smelled inside the house. -Do not put any furniture outside at any time.
host_about:
Susan is the owner and a regular Airbnb traveler, and Natalia is the property manager and handles all booking inquiries.

Susan: I own my own business and am from Austin, TX.  I love to travel - I'm trying to get around to seeing as much as I can!  I've traveled to all fifty states and twenty-three countries.

I've been renting out my home for about 7 years now and love meeting the many people from all over, as well as hearing their stories why they're visiting Austin.  We hope you'll come experience our hospitality and beautiful home.

name: Central Cottage with bikes!
summary: Private, detached cottage in central Austin, ideal for a couple looking for a quiet accommodation with easy access to all that Austin has to offer.
space: Clean, private cottage with lots of light in peaceful, tree-lined Ridgelea neighborhood in central Austin, five miles from downtown.  The cottage is a separate building behind our house, so you have lots of privacy, though we are usually on-site if you have questions or want to visit with us.  It shares a garden courtyard with our residence.  Fully-functioning, 400 square-foot residential space with three rooms:  sleeping area with loveseat, full kitchen, and bath with shower. Queen-size, comfortable bed with pillow top mattress sleeps two.  Fresh bed and bath linens provided.   Kitchen has a table for two next to a sunny window, gas stove, full-size fridge, microwave, coffee maker, toaster and blender.  We provide coffee, sugar and milk.  There is cooking oil and basic seasonings.  The kitchen is fully stocked with dishes, cutlery, glasses, coffee cups, pots/pans and utensils including cooking knives, blender and a corkscrew.      Bathroom has plenty of counter space and a closet.  Bl

neighborhood_overview: Walking distance to the original Kerbey Lane Cafe (open late).  Central Market is less than a mile away and walkable, but bike or car is recommended.  Close to Shoal Creek Greenbelt and bike routes.  We are in Central Austin, which is near 35th Street and Loop 1 (Mopac Expressway).  Our neighborhood is a 1940s central Austin residential area about 5 miles from downtown and SoCo/tourist attractions.
notes: We operate under City of Austin Short Term Rental License in compliance with City of Austin ordinance and code. View photos to see operating permit.
transit: ******PLEASE NOTE LOCATION AND DISTANCE/TRAVEL TIMES BELOW.  ******MOST OF OUR GUESTS HAVE OR RENT CARS.  Downtown and Barton Springs are bikeable.  You can bike to SoCo, but can be traffic and there is a long hill.  It's fast and easy to take one of the many rideshare options, including Uber and Lyft.  Rideshare to downtown is about $12 plus tip.  Pro tip:  rideshares mean you don't have to find a parking space!   Bike to downtown:  25-30 minutes (5 miles) Drive to downtown/SoCo area: 15 minutes (5-6 miles) Transport other than the bikes is recommended at night, but we do have lights.
access: We have a choice of five bikes you may borrow (see photos.)  There are three hybrids, two of which fit most riders and one of which fits average to shorter riders.  There is a vintage (1973) single speed Schwinn Speedster that fits taller riders and another vintage single speed that fits average size riders. Each bike has a lock and spare tube/repair kit.  We have three helmets available. Fast wifi, 37" flat screen TV with Roku, with streaming channels including Netflix, local TV channels.  Stereo with iPhone cable and CD player, propane and charcoal grill, iron and ironing board, hair dryer, picnic backpack. There is ample parking on the street and you should be able to park in front of our house. Please DO NOT park in our driveway except for loading and unloading.
interaction: We enjoy meeting our guests, offering recommendations on places to eat and things to do, making new friends and being hosts, but we respect your privacy too. A good guide for gathering things to do in Austin:  (Website hidden by Airbnb)
house_rules: Please park on the street and ask your visitors to do so as well.  Do not park in our driveway except for loading and unloading.   Please turn the AC/heater OFF when you leave for more than an hour.   Please help us save water and energy and hang/re-use towels.
host_about: Easy-going couple, longtime residents of Austin, we love Austin music and theatre. Andy is into bicycles and sometimes rides his bike to work.  Ellen helps run a small local theatre company.  We both have day jobs as legal professionals.

name: Simple 2/2 in Central Austin
space: Simply furnished 2/2 next to UT Austin campus. Stained concrete floors. Granite counter tops. 2 parking spaces. W/D. Wireless internet. Trash valet certain mornings.  One bedroom with queen size bed and a loveseat; One bedroom with full size futon; Twin size futon in living room. If you're able to bring additional bedding, this apartment could fairly easily fit 6 people. It's a great location for SXSW, ACL, as well as just about any event that's happening in central Austin. Downtown hotels can get a little pricey at times. Here, you'd only be a 5 minute drive/cab or bus ride to downtown AND you'd have an entire apartment all to yourself! There's also a brand new awesome Trailer Park Eatery literally right outside of the apartment. All sorts of yummy deliciousness!

name: Welcoming East Austin Guest Suite
summary: Austin weekends & events await you in this spacious guest room with private entrance & private bathroom. Walk to downtown, University of Texas and east side entertainment districts, but come home to a quiet retreat.
space: Welcome to Casa Leona! We want you to fall in love with Austin. Please be my guest in the spacious home that I share with two housemates and one cat. Staying this close to Downtown Austin puts you in the heart of activity at the University of Texas, the state capitol, the entertainment districts and the festival and conference hubs. Yet, it's also a peaceful, quiet retreat from those same fun places and events. We are in easy walking distance to great coffee shops, pubs and a variety of restaurants and food trailers. The Guest Suite: Spacious and private guest suite is 500 sq.ft and has a private entrance and patio. It is furnished with a queen bed, couch, a few chairs, and a few patio chairs outside. The room includes a mini kitchen with a refrigerator and teapot. You will have a private (small) bathroom with sink, toilet and shower (no bath tub). The room has a stereo and wifi, but no TV. neighborhood_overview: Central East Austin has been through it all. The amazing public art and beautiful people are a reflection of the history of an often poor, but always  proud community.  We're in a traditionally African American neighborhood, but now is a cultural blend reflecting the city today. Gentrification is an ongoing issue and challenge (and opportunity) here. I am proud of this neighborhood and fortunate to have lived here since 2000.
notes: Smoking is ok on the porch or patio.
transit: Public transportation: Yes, it's  is available, but not up to par for a city of this size.  Here's the online trip planner: (URL HIDDEN) We are a 2-3 block walk to 4 busstops. Austin has one rail line. The closest stop is about 1 mile from here. Walking/biking: this is a walkable city, but beware of being super ambitious with your walk. If you walk to an event at UT, you might be tired when you arrive. You can walk to the East 6th Street or Manor Road entertainment/restaurants (almost) no sweat! Renting a bike might just be the way to go! I recommend (URL HIDDEN) A bike will get you downtown or to UT campus with a smile on your face and in your heart. Be very careful! Not all drivers are as nice or aware as you! Taxi/Uber/Lyft: Yes. Uber & Lyft drivers are always available. You can wave to hail a cab downtown, but you have to call from my house (I use 1-800-taxi-cab). My best suggestion for around town and the airport is to cue the Uber or Lyft app.  Driving a car: This can be very hel
access: Guests have access to your own private suite, but not the common areas of the house. If you need kitchen or laundry room access, we can arrange it on an individual basis. You will also have access to all the outdoor spaces (front porch and courtyard by your suite).
interaction: I'd love to get to know you a little or a lot, based on our plans and needs at the time of your visit. I'm an experienced host and my goal is for you to be as comfortable as possible.
house_rules: Be open to cats, no pet allergies.  It's ok to smoke on the patio, but not inside. We observe quiet hours after 10pm on weeknights.  We live here. We will all be living together. Please be respectful to people and property.  Have fun!
host_about:
I have lived here in East Austin since 2000 and I am very pleased to welcome you! I work mostly from home, but also from my office downtown. I love travel, walking, hiking, reading, coffee, food and just doing not much at all :-)
Hosting has been a highlight of my life since 2015. I feel truly privileged to have met the amazing people who have stayed with me and honored to call some former guests my current friends.

name: South Shore Condo on Lady Bird Lake
summary: 1/1 condo facing a park in gated community on the south shore of Lady Bird Lake. 10 miles to the airport/COTA and 2 miles to downtown, SOCO and the 6th Street party district. 25 miles to the Dripping Springs wedding venues. Complex offers a pool, lakeside dock and access to the new Boardwalk trail. STR licensed by the City of Austin. 021899
space: Gorgeous 1/1 condo on the south shore of Lady Bird Lake. 10 miles from the airport and 2 to downtown, South Congress and 6th Street.  Complex offers free parking, a pool, lakeside dock and access to the new Boardwalk trail. Condo is just east of I-35 and 20 minutes from the Circuit of the Americas and 25 to the Dripping Springs wedding venues. Our condo is located within a gated community just off of Riverside Drive in the up and coming South Shore District with free parking and a bus stop 1/3 of a mile away. Mexican food and margaritas across the street at Baby Acapulco's and a 24-hour coffee shop Buzz Mill is a short walk away. The East Riverside corridor is becoming the new hot spot in Austin with legendary live music club Emo's  relocating from 6th street to within walking distance of our condo. Unit features beautiful tile floors, a private courtyard facing the park with a partial view of the lake and access to the community pool and lakeside dock. Enjoy a drink and maybe the famo

neighborhood_overview: The Southshore District is an up and coming area that is super convenient to I-35, downtown, SOCO, COTA and the airport. There are restaurants, clubs, and parkland all within walking distance of our condo. Starbucks, Walgreens, Chipotle, Mour Cafe, Chilantro and Mod Pizza are a few of the new options within walking distance.
notes: My insurance policy requires that both parties sign a rental agreement. It is a simple online process and the agreement will be emailed to you after booking. The rental rules you agree to are listed below. RENTAL RULES 1.Smoking is NOT allowed inside unit. Smoking is allowed outside only. 2.Please respect your neighbors and keep noise to a minimum. No parties, gatherings, loud music/TV etc.  3.Pool Hours are 8 AM to 10 PM and absolutely no glass allowed at pool. 4.People other than those in the Guest party set forth above may not stay overnight in the property.  Any other person in the property is the sole responsibility of Guest. 5.All of the units are privately owned; the owners are not responsible for any accidents, injuries or illness that occurs while on the premises or its facilities. The Homeowners are not responsible for the loss of personal belongings or valuables of the guest. By accepting this reservation, it is agreed that all guests are expressly assuming the risk of any h
transit: There is a bus stop 1/4 mile away with easy access to downtown. The Airport Flyer has a stop 1/2 mile away on East Riverside that will take you to or from ABIA for $1.75. UBER and Lyft are available but download the Ride Austin app as they are a nice local alternative.
access: The condo is all yours and you have access to a community pool and lakeside dock. There is also a nice public park right outside our fence with paddle board and kayak rentals.
interaction: I will give you an access code to our keypad and allow you to check yourself in.  You may always call or text me with any concern and I will provide you with several phone numbers.
house_rules: 1. No parties, gatherings or loud music. Please respect your neighbors! 2. Parking is for residents only, including you as our guest. If you have any visitors, (see above) they must park on the street and walk in.  3. No smoking in the condo. (you may smoke on the back patio) 4. No Pets allowed.  5. Check in at 3 PM (flexible) 6. Check out at noon (flexible) 7. Please put recyclables in blue bin on back patio. 8. Please help us conserve by using minimal towels and bedding. 9. The City of Austin bans use of ALL handheld devices while driving. This includes phones, GPS devices etc. Fines can be as high as $500.
host_about: I am an Austin native and can't imagine living anywhere else. I  am retired from the Austin Fire Department after 28 years and was the Lieutenant in charge of Engine 5-C on the east side for the last 15.  I love Austin and know this great city inside and out! I can recommend everything from a killer BBQ joint, great Tex-Mex or the best vegetarian restaurant in town.I can tell you where to go (and where not to go) to make your stay with us the best it can be.

name: PRIVATE COTTAGE APT-Central Austin
summary: Private apartment tucked away in historic lush West Austin neighborhood.  Five minutes to downtown, close to lake, bike and hike trails and lots of great restaurants.
space: Cottage Apartment in desirable Tarrytown neighborhood.  With everything you need for short or longer stay, the apartment is of new construction, designer decorated with one bedroom (queen bed) and pull out sofa bed (queen) in living area, full bath, kitchen and washer/dryer, TV, DVD player and wifi.  Light breakfast, bottled water, fruit, coffee and tea are stocked in the kitchen upon arrival.  All linens and towels including bathing towels for swimming are provided.  For the warm summer months, a lovely public pool sits at the end of the block,  a three minute walk away.  Only 5 min. drive to downtown, and convenient to mass transit, you are also walking distance to lake and hike and bike trails.  Perfect for ACL or neighborhood stroll to the lake. neighborhood_overview: My street borders Williamson Creek, and many of my neighbors also enjoy the natural spaces behind their homes. You'll see a lot of dog-walkers, runners with dogs, fathers with baby carriages and dogs in tow. My neighbors are kind, friendly and willing to assist if there's a need. A family of owls live along the creek behind our homes. Hawks are also frequent visitors. It's quiet, and peaceful. Inside the home you're protected from general neighborhood sounds. This is a walking neighborhood bordered by other small neighborhoods and many iconic South Austin points of interest. I live in close proximity to many of these gems. Most of them are within a mile, a 15 minute walk. You'll find a list in the Guidebook, and a long list of guest and host-recommended places printed out in the House Manual in your room. I also send a Welcome letter upon booking, with suggestions taken from these lists. I also post popular places on the fridge!
notes: HOTEL OCCUPANCY TAX. This 9% City of Austin hotel tax is collected upon arrival or added to reservation. This tax is different from the 6% State Tax Airbnb collects when you book. From the City of Austin website: "The City of Austin’s Hotel Occupancy Tax rate is 9 percent, comprised of a 7 percent occupancy tax and an additional 2 percent venue project tax. The City’s tax is IN ADDITION to the 6 percent rate imposed by the State of Texas, which must be remitted separately to the State." PETS: This room is a Pet-Free Zone. Please know that while I sometimes host guests with pets, I keep my house and common areas free of dander for guests who need a clean, dander-free space. If you’d like to bring your pet, please check out my other listing, “South Austin Charmer on Greenspace, 4 miles to DT." OTHER GUESTS: Sometimes I have other guests staying in my home. The bedrooms are well insulated, and are situated next to each other at the end of a hall. My House Rules reinforce to my guests the
transit: Before we get to "getting around," I recommend checking out "Culturemap" for all-things Austin, as well as "EaterAustin" for the latest and greatest food offerings. "Culturemap" is an up-to-date online magazine covering a multitude of cultural events and happenings, with helpful hints on restaurants, bars, clubs and transportation options. GETTING AROUND BY CAR My house is located 5 minutes from all major street and highway routes leading downtown as well as all points east, west, north and south. I'm a mile from Hwy 71/290 (Ben White Blvd), which connects you, in minutes, to I-35, MoPac (Loop 1) and the three major street routes leading downtown, South Lamar, South First and Congress Avenue. It's a convenient location for getting around, one of the steady comments I get from guests! BUSSES CapMetro (MetroBus) Busses in Austin are well-maintained and on-time. They pick up every 10-15 minutes. It's a 5 minute walk from my home to the closest bus stop, and a 40-minute ride to downtown. R
access: Guests are free to access the big deck overlooking a flowering rock garden and bird sanctuary. The shared bath is cleaned daily. The rest of the house is for private use. Kitchen use for meal preparation is available upon request for reservations longer than 5 days. The living room is available for extra sleeping during festivals (extra person fees apply). The couch is wide enough to accommodate one person and is very comfortable. The cushions are thick, sturdy and soft. The area can be curtained off for privacy. There's room for one or two additional people on a queen-size airbed (can be provided on request). The floor of the living room is carpeted, with a 1/2" foam pad supporting it.
interaction: I truly enjoy helping my guests make the most of their stay.  That said I'll respect your privacy and ask that you do the same for me. If time allows I hope we get to know each other a little before you leave. It's one of the truly satisfying aspects of being a host. :) WORK MODE I work from home and spend a good bit of my time in my office, situated just off the deck and dining area. If you need something I'm happy to help! Just ask. NEW TO THE CITY? If time permits I try to block out a little time at check-in to answer questions for newcomers to the city. I'm happy to sit down with you and look up places of interest, restaurants and music venues and give logistical support. If you're new to the city and would like this kind of help, please let me know! HOST CONTACT I'm available by text and phone and can usually respond within 15 minutes. John, my co-host and I are happy to help if you have questions about places to check out. I recommend using the Airbnb app for communication as it
house_rules: HOUSE RULES EXTRA GUESTS: Once you arrive in my home, I don't allow guests to bring friends, acquaintances or any other person into my home, for any reason, unless you've cleared it with me first, at least 48 hours in advance. I reserve the right to meet this person, and verify their identity, BEFORE they are allowed in my home. I reserve the right to decline your request. No approved guest (approved by me only) will be allowed to stay overnight UNTIL any extra-person fees have been paid. If you violate this safety and security rule, you will be asked to leave immediately, you will face serious penalties and you will forfeit the remainder of your reservation fees. HOME SECURITY: As required by Airbnb, I'm letting you know that my home has a home monitoring system which captures clips of activity in the living room, hall and office area. These are private spaces. An active exterior security camera captures activity at the door. There is no monitoring in either of the bedrooms or the bat
host_about:
I'm a performing songwriter, musician. Have lived in Austin since 2005. Before that lived in Florida and raised a son. I'm originally from New England.

I keep a tidy house and it tends to stay quiet and low key. No drama, no nonsense. I'm busy and stay focused on my career, but I love to meet new people.

My house has a calm, sweet vibe to it.

Airbnb will not allow me to change the address. It's on Ruiz St. 78723
space: A 4 bedroom, 3 full and 2 half bath, 3 story, 3700 ft2 home in Mueller. The photos on this site are of my other property. I'm happy to take video or photos of this new house; just haven't done it yet! Other features include gourmet kitchen, wine fridge, jacuzzi tub, high ceilings, custom finishes throughout..  The house has wireless, hardwood floors, no spiked heels inside, sprinkler system, offstreet parking garage, though plenty of parking in front. One tempurpedic king bed in master, another king in the other master, two additional bedrooms with queen beds. Two parakeets will stay here; so please be willing to care for them.  I have a small toy poodle that will stay with a friend.  The house is professionally cleaned twice a week and will be prior to and after rental.  If your group would like midweek cleaning, that can be arranged for $170 basic cleaning (no laundry or sheet changes). Public transportation is available 1 block away. look up (Website hidden by Airbnb)
