name: Lovely chic 2 Bdrm Downtown whereAirbnb CEO stays
summary: DOWN-TOWN, 1.9 miles from Convention Center. Beautiful elegant yet rustic shabby-chic bungalow house wt back deck in Austin's loveliest neighborhood. A refuge away from the world next to a great park. Walking distance to Whole Foods & amazing restaurants and shops. One of top 3 most loved locations in Austin. Tons of art/design books and lovely antiques.  SUPER cozy beds, big kitchen for cooking, big back deck for relaxing & sitting outside at night wt a glass of wine.
space: My first guest was the Airbnb CEO Brian Chesky. In the stunning downtown historic neighborhood of Clarksville, at 12th & lamar, walking distance to Whole Foods, great cafes,Town Lake Trail and downtown bars. Tucked away on a quiet dead end street. Most beautiful neighborhood ever. Beautiful, quaint bungalow home in the lovely historic neighborhood of Clarksville, 4 blocks from Whole Foods World Headquarters. Approx 1 mile from downtown bars and music venues, tucked away on a private dead-end street, next to a small park. Nearby are: Cafe Medici, Jeffrey's, Fresh Plus Grocery, Zocalo Cafe, Wink, Castle Hill Fitness, Black Swan yoga, etc. 1.2 miles from the Town Lake Hike and Bike Trail and Zilker Park. 1.2 miles from University of Texas or the Capitol. 1 amazing king bed. 1 queen bed, 2 sofas. 1 bathroom. In the stunning downtown historic neighborhood of Clarksville, at 12th & lamar, walking distance to Whole Foods, great cafes,Town Lake Trail and downtown bars. Tucked away on a quiet dead end street. name: The Travis Heights Tree House
space: The Travis Heights Tree House is a  lovely studio in the desirable Travis Heights neighborhood.  Open and airy the studio feels spacious with 10' high ceilings.  The kitchen has plenty of storage, bamboo counter tops, an electric range, coffeepot and microwave. The bathroom is beautifully tiled with subway tile and has a bath and plenty of storage as well.  The living area is cozy and comfortable and flooded with natural light.   The large, private deck is surrounded by trees and the perfect place to enjoy your morning coffee or evening cocktail.  Tucked in on a double lot the Tree House affords you both privacy and a prime location. Lady Bird Lake is a short walk from the studio where you can hike, bike, rent a canoe or kayak or eat at one of the many restaurants or food trailers.   Just down the hill, Big Stacy Pool is open year round and heated in the winter.  S. Congress is a short 1/2 mile walk away with many excellent restaurants, shops and the world famous Continental Club.   Fr

name: Living the Dream on Richardine
summary: Close to everything East Austin. Austin Bouldering Project, Hard Luck Lounge, East Austin Succulents, SaTen, Eden East, Springdale Farms, Drink Daily Greens, Friends&Allies Brewery, The Austin Shaker. A short #RideAustin trip to East 6th. A block from the bus line that goes straight downtown if Dirty 6th is your thing. We live a really comfortable life here with our dog, Ronnie James Dio. Our neighborhood is real, not a Disney movie. But we dig it. All are welcome. Come visit.
space: Our house is a standard 1960's ranch with an open kitchen/living room. It's a really comfortable space that has lots of natural shade from large trees in the yard. The room has a double bed with a twin mattress underneath that can q add space for a third body to sleep. Funky old antique furniture from my relatives in small town Mississippi (where Elvis was born!). We have a 70 passenger school bus in the driveway that will soon be an additional guest house. We also have a small DIY music studio in the back yard if you feel the need to lay down a few tracks while you're here.

host_about: i'm old and young. i am happy and also sometimes sad. i love to sit at home and have people drift in and out and talk and drink and leave and return and change the subject. i quit smoking but i still totally want a drag of your cigarette but i won't take one. my middle name is no middle name. my partner is a dope old dude who makes a mean cup of coffee. my dog is so metal it hurts.

summary: 2br/2ba house in the heart of it all, surrounded by great bars, restaurants and venues. East 2nd Main House offers you a hub that's less than a half mile to the Austin Convention Center and Hilton, and less than a mile to JW Marriott. Its the perfect spot for business or pleasure, and comfortably sleeps four in beds.
space: This property is a licensed Short Term Rental. Please see photos for STR license number. 2 Bedroom, 2 Bathroom, Sleeps 4 Whether you are visiting family, or in town for business or pleasure, your Austin accommodations have never been so convenient and comfortable. This home was originally built in 1902, and was completely remodeled in 2009, designed to maintain its old world charm while providing modern amenities. East 2nd Main House is one block east of downtown Austin in an eclectic neighborhood. It is bright and airy with 10-foot ceilings throughout, vaulted ceilings in the master bedroom and many windows providing ample natural light. A mere five blocks from Austin’s famous 6th Street district, and within walking distance to fine dining, coffee houses and art galleries, it’s easy to say that this home is in a fantastic location. notes: This home is located downtown, just east of Interstate 35.
transit: This location is within walking distance to lots of great places. All major ride-share companies, like Lyft, Uber operate in Austin. We also have Ride Austin, a local ride share company, as well as Capital Metro public transit operating busses, paratransit services and a commuter rail system known as the Capital MetroRail.
access: There is an electronic deadbolt on the entrance of this home. A unique access code will be provided to you in a set of arrival instruction sent via email.
interaction: We are Emerson Guest Properties, a boutique rental management company based in Austin, Texas, We hope to exceed guest expectations by being respectful of our guests' privacy, while remaining available for their needs throughout any given reservation.
house_rules: 1.CHECK-IN TIME IS AFTER 4PM CST AND CHECK-OUT IS 11AM CST. No early check in without owners’ permission. We will generally leave the key in a combo box at the property. Check out time is firm unless permission is specifically given for an alternate time. 2.This is a NON SMOKING home. Smoking is permitted outside. No pets are permitted without permission from owners. (URL HIDDEN) DEPOSIT- A damage/reservation deposit of $100. This must be received at the time of booking the reservation. The deposit automatically converts to a security/damage deposit upon arrival. The deposit is NOT applied toward rent; however, it is fully  refundable within five (5) days of departure, provided the following provisions  are met: No damage is done to home or its contents, beyond normal wear and tear.  b.All debris, rubbish and discards are placed in outside trash bin, and soiled  dishes are placed in the dishwasher and cleaned. c.All keys are returned to combo box. d.All charges accrued during the stay
host_about:
I am an El Paso native and John is from Sheboygan, WI! We have lived in Central East Austin for about six years. We enjoy our neighborhood and want you to experience everything Austin has to offer from great restaurants and entertainment to  SXSW, ACL, X Games and Formula 1. Our dog Azore loves guests and will often greet them with barks followed by licks. 

Our favorite thing to do on a Sunday morning is to walk the dog on the hike and bike trail, stop at the Rowing Center to enjoy the view of the lake, then have breakfast at Jo's Coffee on West 2nd Street and walk back home through downtown. Cenote, which is just three blocks away is our neighborhood staple. It's great for breakfast, lunch and dinner and offers a nice beer and wine list. If you are up for a walk, head over to East End Wines, order a bottle of wine and dine from the trailer in the parking lot - Three Little Pigs. It's one of my favorite outings.

Let me know what you are interested in and I am happy to offer suggestions. This city is lots of fun and I would love to help you maximize your enjoyment!

Brooke with Emerson Guest Properties manages my rentals for me. She'll answer any questions you may have both before, during and after the reservation process, provide all the arrival info you'll need, and will always be available during your stay. Thanks!

name: Beautiful East Austin House
summary: Enjoy Austin while staying in a beautiful, clean, modern home in a wonderful, walk-able neighborhood.  The open concept living space and large outdoor patio with fire pit and hammocks are perfect for relaxing at the end of the day.  This is East Austin at its finest!
space: Enjoy Austin while staying in this beautiful, fun, creative 2 bedroom and 1  bathroom house located a few short blocks from Downtown Austin.   Walk out the front door into a vibrant Eastside neighborhood with local restaurants, dive bars and historic institutions such as The Victory Grill, a legendary juke joint from the 1930's.  It's a short walk to downtown and the East 6th St. music scene.  There's easy access to downtown, UT campus and F1 by bus, walking, pedi-cab, bike or taxi.  The airport is 15 minutes away, and sometimes I'm able to help with pick-up and drop-off. You will love the house,  it's modern and eclectic.    The large guest room is upstairs and has a huge window and lots of light.  There is one queen bed, and a full size Aero-bed is available upon request.   There is a comfortable chair, desk and shelves.  The full bathroom is shared with the host.  The open concept living space is perfect for entertaining and enjoying a meal.   The front yard has custom landscaping w

neighborhood_overview: Being able to walk downtown cannot be beat.  When Austin traffic is at its most crazy, I'm always glad I can get around without even needing a bike.   The neighborhood restaurants are great, check out Blue Dahlia for open faced sandwiches, fresh salads and their delectable blueberry blintzes.  The house is 4 blocks from Franklin BBQ--voted best in the USA.
transit: Walk, bike, bus, taxi, pedi-cab, drive...  There is a reserved driveway parking spot for guests if you rent a car.
access: In addition to their private bedroom, guest are welcome to use the public areas of the house: living room, dining room, kitchen and outdoor areas.
interaction: I follow my guest's lead in terms of interaction.   I have had guests come to Austin for business, and they just needed a quiet place to unwind at the end of the day.  On the other end of the spectrum, I've hosted Icelandic folk singers who wanted me to show them around East Austin, and we hung out every night.
house_rules: This house is my home...please be respectful.    No smoking indoors, and please use ashtrays if smoking outside.  I don't charge extra for clean up, and so far no guests have made me sorry about this policy.
host_about:
Some of my favorite experiences in life occurred when I was traveling around the world, and now I welcome the chance to host other travelers in my home in Central East Austin.  I've had the good fortune to live and work in Vienna, Tel Aviv, Tai Pei, and Bergama, Turkey.  My favorite travel destinations have been Thailand and India (Goa is at the top of my list.)   I have tried to create a "mini-Goa" in my backyard with hammocks and a relaxing vibe.  Alas, no Indian Ocean is nearby but Barton Springs is a 10 minute bike ride and Town Lake is even closer.

Please feel free to contact me with questions about the house and neighborhood.  I've hosted musicians for SXSW since 2010, and it has been a lot of fun!

summary: Beautiful condo in the heart of downtown Austin within walking distance to Capitol Building, Austin City Limits shuttles, 6th Street, all of SxSW, Funky South Congress Avenue, horse carriage rides, and all the best restaurants and bars. space: This open, contemporary condo is right in 78701, the heart of downtown Austin. There's really no better location in the city.  It is a safe and quiet luxury condominium building, with 24 hour security, and is within walking distance to the best Austin has to offer. It is a 5-10 minute walk to our best restaurants, the Capitol building, historic Congress Avenue, the 6th Street music scene, the bats at the Congress Bridge, and all of the sites that downtown Austin has to offer. The 13th floor rooftop terrace offers views of the Capitol Building and the downtown skyline, and is a great place to relax with a glass of wine.  The condo is clean, non-smoking, sleek and modern. There is a washer and dryer, TV and wifi. I would love to host you for 30+ days. Please contact me if interested!

space: Comfortable furnishings, high ceilings, natural light and wood floors welcomes you to this beautiful Austin home. Our home is a sanctuary to us and we would love to share that with you. There is an awesome deck above you where you are welcome to ignite and inhale.  Rule #3: there is no rule #3.  Rule #4: No Pets. Well, MAYBE a dog, but we'd have to talk about it. Also, Wallace, my dog, has the run of the property. He is the sweetest creature, best dog ever. It's possible he might bark at you, but hey, it's his job. Generally he'll be in the house when you're coming and going.  Rule #5: I'll give you a key so you can lock up while you're away. I ask that you respect the private areas of the property.  Rule #6: Please, no parties or behavior that would make one of our neighbors want to call the police.  Rule #7: Be cool with the innerwebs. No illegal downloading/abuse of internet privileges.  Rule #8: towel hooks on the bathroom door - - use 'em.  Rule #9: If I think of other rules, I'll add them. Meantime, please let me know what I can do to make
host_about: I like Ben Franklin's quote about beer — it's proof that "God loves us and wants us to be happy," (define God in that sentence in what ever way makes you most comfortable). Sharing the city of Austin is one of my favorite things about being a host. I like to treat my Airbnb guests the way I'd treat friends or family. My roots are southern, but I am not a Texan. I consider myself a resident of the enlightened city-state of Austin and the planet Earth, and am at home generally in any college town. I think the Beatles were right, love is all you need. Dogs rule, cats make me sneeze. I put this fortune cookie fortune on my bulletin board: "Friends are more valuable than money."

neighborhood_overview: The main road in the Zilker neighborhood is South Lamar, which is bustling with activity. The guesthouse is 1 mile to Barton Springs and Zilker Park, 1.5 miles to legendary music venues Continental Club and The Broken Spoke, 2.5 miles to downtown. The Alamo South movie theater is a pleasant 10-15 minute walk. South Lamar has a burgeoning restaurant and bar scene. For a good overview, go to the DO512 website and search for an article titled What to Do on South Lamar.  Be sure to check out our Airbnb Guidebook with tips on restaurants, bars, stores and venues in the area! It is not comprehensive, but it will give you a good taste of the neighborhood. The NY Times Frugal Traveler has a great article on how to spend a weekend in Austin for $100 (excluding lodging). The writer enjoyed lots of great places and activities, including some of our faves. Search for "frugal traveler blog austin." For another good article in the NY Times travel section, search for "36 hours in Austin."
notes: [City of Austin Short-Term Rental Operating License # 022105] Note that we do not charge a cleaning fee.
transit: Many of our guests walk to their destinations, many being within a mile or two. It's a short walk to several Cap Metro bus lines that go downtown and to points beyond. Austin has several ride-sharing services. They are cheaper than cabs and faster than calling for a cab. We love RideAustin, a nonprofit that gives back to the community in many ways. Biking is a good way to get around town. Barton Springs Bike Rental offers convenient drop-off / pick-up service. Reservations recommended, especially on weekends and for special events.
access: Feel free to relax on the patio. If you run into the dogs, they are Coco (miniature pinscher, poor vision), Rusty (chihuahua, deaf) and Alice (scruffy mutt, mostly deaf). They are small, old, easygoing dogs.
interaction: If you need anything during your stay, please text or call me, or just knock on the door.
house_rules: - AirBNB is based on trust and transparency, and we want our guests to be a good match for our property. We expect you to have an AirBNB profile that uses your real name and information, a clear photo, and a rental request with good details.  - Maximum capacity is two. No additional guests permitted overnight. - If you are visiting with a second person, please let us know that person's full name. - Check-in 3pm, check-out 12pm. Often we can be flexible on that, so if your times differ, please let us know. - No smoking inside the guest house.  - No pets.   - If you empty your trash, use the small green cart for trash and the large blue cart for recycling. - Close the backyard gate securely when you come and go.  - Base rate increases for major festivals.
host_about: Transplants from Chicago, we have lived in Austin since 2007 and love it! Jaime is an editor for a nonprofit and works from home. Mike is a carpenter who works around town. Our little dogs (Rusty, Coco & Alice) are sweet but somewhat aloof seniors. We enjoy live music, long walks, great microbrews, local eateries (including vegetarian friendly) and the funky, creative, friendly vibe that makes Austin so unique. We also love exploring our city and are happy to share tips with our guests.

neighborhood_overview: Galindo neighborhood is in the "hip" part of South Austin, within 2 miles to Hike and bike trail, Downtown Austin,  SOCO, S.1st, and S.Lamar.  Less than 3 miles to Zilker Park, ACL FEST.  78704 area is close to many local music venues Downtown @ 6th Street, Rainey Street, and even closer  are ABGC beer garden/live music/food, The Continental Club, Saxon Pub, One to One,Gueros outside venue, Opal Devines, Maria's Taco's, Horseshoe Lounge, Opa Coffee/Wine bar. Many other restaurants, coffee shops, bars are very closeby. Galindo is very quiet and many neighbors in my area have been residing there for decades. Within walking distance, options include Torchy's Tacos, coffee shops, a wine/tapas cafe, a new beer brew pub ABGBC, numerous Mexican restaurants, unique shops on S. 1st, SOCO.......less than 1.5 miles to DT as it is a straight shot down S. 1st. Parking is safe on the street. This backyard is an oasis to return to after massive stimuli enjoying Austin!
notes: 9% City of Austin  STR Hotel Tax not included in your Airbnb bill is due in cash upon check in.  NO swimming in above ground pool. Immediate eviction if this rule is broken. Event rates for SXSW, ACL Fest, and F1 race are higher than daily rates.
transit: Parking is safe on street in front of my home.  Easily accessible to both bus lines on S. 1st and on S. 5th, only minutes walking to the bus stops with very short ride to DT Austin.  From the airport to my home, taxi  is about $30 with tip and takes 15 to 30 minutes depending on traffic. Buses are also available from the airport to DT and then grab either southbound bus on S. 1st or S. 5th to Cumberland St........couple minute walk home from there.  More info once you have booked the space.
access: Check in is simple and I will give you more instructions after your confirmation. Guests are free to come and go independently with their own key at any time. Well lit up at night with lanspdscape lights and a motion sensor light at gate.
interaction: I am happy to give you all your space and privacy with only minimal contact if you like. I  am willing to assist you about the area,  our musical history, the hill country, and with any assistance required.
house_rules: Only 2 adults maximum. No swimming in above the ground pool and must sign waiver releasing me of all liability. No Children. No Pets. No Movie Filming.  I am looking for a respectful renter who is appreciative that I am opening up my personal space. No loud music,smoking ok outside of the cottage, parking in from on curb, report any damages, problems or issues to me, no matter how small. Only 2 guests and no more.
host_about:
I enjoy music, photography, travel, cactus/succulents, fishing/boating, the Oaxacan Pacific coast and meeting interesting people. I have followed Austin's music scene since the 70's Armadillo World Headquarters days. I especially enjoy all the Texas singer/songwriters who put Austin on the musical map. Also, I love New Orleans music  which has a deep, rich history  and a sound that transcends me in time. My interests cover from Buddy Holly to Buddy Bolden,  from Townes to Dr John, and Shinyribs to Trombone Shorty.  My musical tastes cover rock, country, R & B, reggae, blues, jazz, conjunto/Tex Mex, Mexican, African, Cuban, Latin, Big Band, and classical. I own and operate the South First Food Court which is in a unique area peppered with many mostly local Austin independent businesses, coffee shops,restaurants,and music stories.  Torchy's Tacos, Summermoon coffee shop, are just a short walk down the hill to S. 1st from my home. I am very close to SoCo, S. Lamar, Zilker Park, and Downtown.
I have had very satisfied  airbnb guests from all over the world, all ages, different backgrounds and cultures who enjoy a clean, moderately priced,  private stay in a very beautiful and peaceful backyard in a quiet neighborhood which is close to many of Austin's choice spots.
I enjoy working with plants......cactus, succulents,bromeliads especially. I have been creating cactus bowls that pass on a humorous, satirical, political, poke in the eye.   I use found objects, kid's unwanted, broken, exhausted or abandoned toys, Mexican chotzkies, etc. My backyard reflects many of my passions about plants .
Check out Evangeline's , Broken Spoke, Saxon Pub, Continental Club, Green Pastures, the East Austin scene, Rainey St., Ski Shores, cruise Lake Austin in a boat, Pace Bend Park,the Hill Country, Gruene Hall,  Lockhart BBQ, Rubys BBQ, Sandy's Burgers, swim Barton Springs,hit the Botanical garden,and check out the Austin Chronicle as well as all the new trendy bars/ restaurants....

name: Carriage House Apartment
space: This large, one BR apartment in the eclectic, historic West Austin neighborhood of Clarksville has the best of Austin a short walk away. The Carriage House is an entirely separate building. The entrance is completely private with a separate address. Parking is for guests only directly in front of the building. The large living room, spacious bedroom and dining area allow you to spread out and make yourselves at home. The galley-shaped kitchen is ideal for those who like to cook.  You'll be centrally located, within walking distance to stores, shops and restaurants. There's a great grocery store, called Fresh Plus, just one block away. Walk to downtown in 30 minutes or less. City bus stops are also just down the street. Two blocks away you can catch a bus to/from the University of Texas campus. The Carriage House is incredibly close to everything, yet quiet, private, spacious and comfortable.

host_about:

I love good food, and know all of the great places to eat in Austin.  I also love to see any film that is playing at the Violet Crown Theater.

The kitchen is fully equipped and you’re welcome to cook up a storm. This is a private room in a comfy house with a new Queen Size bed. I also have a comfy cot if you have a miscellaneous person who wants to tag along. The Skyview neighborhood is just 1/4 mile from North Loop, 3 miles from UT and 5 miles north of downtown—and close to public transportation. host_about:
Having company is a great guilty pleasure. That's why I'm an AirBnB host. How fun to have new potential friends show up on my doorstep! I love to talk about my town and the Central Texas area. If you need advice about good Tex-Mex or the local museums I can surely help. And if I don't know the answer I bet I know someone who does. 
I want to hear about where you live. What's the price of eggs? How do you get to work? What does your family usually do for the holidays? Anything you want to share will probably interest me. 
And, if you want to drop your stuff and disappear that's fine too. Just ask if you need anything.
As to my life motto, hmm..."It's all good!"

Upon check out you must: - Load and run the dishwasher, no dirty dishes should be left - Start the washing machine with a load of towels - Place all trash and recycling in outside bins - Lock all doors and windows Thank you for choosing our home!
host_about:
We call our rentals Austin Getaways, and we strive to offer clean, uncluttered, and comfortable rentals at a good value.  Our rentals offer consistent styling and comfort, and if you like one property you'll most likely like the others too!

We've been in Austin for 20 years and love it! We have multiple rentals in Austin, most in Central and North Austin. We enjoy traveling but are more into relaxation than adventure. Whenever there's a group of us going we always prefer to stay in a home versus a hotel. New Zealand might just be our favorite place in the world! 

Amanda has been a licensed Realtor for 15 years and loves her job. If you're looking to buy or sell a house let us know!

Greg is a former electrical engineer but has left that career for greener pastures.

neighborhood_overview: Zilker neighborhood is an established area.  Today Zilker is very popular and homes are in high demand.  Our premises were a dairy until 1955 when the original home was built with mother-in-law unit.  The mother-in-law unit is today the Zilker Guesthouse.  We are 3 miles from downtown and 4 miles from UT.  In Winter you can see downtown from the Guesthouse deck.  Within 2 miles there are over 50 restaurants and bars.  Some of Austin's best are within walking distance.
transit: We have good public transportation, bike rentals, car rental options and ride share companies.  We are blessed to have RideAustin our co-op ride share to add to the mix too.
access: Guests have full access to the guesthouse and gardens.  A large deck is off the guesthouse living room with table, chair and umbrella for Guesthouse guests.

host_about: Semi-retired.  Living in Austin over 35 years.  My interests include animal welfare, cooking and dachshunds.

name: South Austin Cottage 78704 - 2BR
summary: The South Austin Cottage is located approximately 1 and a half miles south of downtown Austin.  You will find many different restaurants, bars and music venues near the cottage.    South Austin is a big part of what makes Austin known for its vibrant uniqueness.
space: We are proud to annouce that our South Austin Cottage has received it's Short Term Rental License #103471 from the City of Austin as required as of Oct. 1, 2012 by the City's Code Compliance Dept. This is a fully-furnished 1951 cottage with original wood floors in old South Austin.  The kitchen is fully equipped.  The bathroom is immaculate and newly remodeled.  The beds have organic cotton sheets and allergen free mattress and pillow covers.  There is a large shaded backyard and a covered porch to get away from the sun and enjoy a cool breeze. There are plenty of restaurants and food trailers within walking distance.  If you like listening to live music or shopping on S. Congress, S. 1st or S. Lamar, this is the perfect place for you.  It is a short biking distance from Zilker Park and 1.5 miles to Town Lake. name: Avenue G Guesthouse in Hyde Park
space: We have a large (400 sq ft) furnished smoke-free guestroom on a quiet street in Austin's historic Hyde Park neighborhood close to the University of Texas and Downtown Austin. The room is on the second floor of our home with a spiral staircase that leads up to your balcony and private entrance. The room is comfortable and quiet, with a queen bed, a sitting area that includes a couch, desk and table as well as an adjacent bath with a dressing area and closet. There are excellent restaurants, grocery, and laundromat within walking distance and we are less than 2 blocks to bus stops that will take you directly downtown or anywhere in Austin. Your suite includes a microwave, refrigerator, bar sink and dishes and cookware along with a hotplate and small appliances. We provide all linens as well as cable tv and fast internet access (wireless and Ethernet). We also have a second bedroom on the same floor for an additional fee.

name: Austin City Limits-Private Pool by Nature Preserve
summary: Serenity and a bottle of Texas wine await you at Casa Mora, a tastefully-decorated modern stone 3 bedroom 2 bath home with a private pool.  Just 20 minutes from Austin by a 7000 acre preserve, it's a perfect base to explore both the culture and energy of Austin and the natural beauty and slower pace of the Texas Hill Country with its lakes, charming town squares, peach orchards, lavender farms, vineyards and breweries. Sit, relax, listen to the chimes and bird watch at your home away from home!
space: Casa Mora features an open floor plan, gourmet kitchen, entertainment center.a computer and printer and a piano. The living space extends outdoors to include a patio and BBQ area, detached game room (with ping pong, Foosball,Smart TV and a double sized fouton) and a fabulous private pool that backs up to the 7000 acre Shield Ranch Nature Preserve.

neighborhood_overview: The quiet is exquisite. Birds and wildlife abound. The neighborhood is secure- there's only one road in and out with only occasional car traffic. Jester King Brewery and Stanley's Farmhouse Pizza -open on weekends- is about a one mile walk away. A stunt ranch, kennel, stables, winery, another brewery and distillery are within a 5 mile radius. And Austin is close by!
notes: We continually make improvements to the property. We recently replaced the double bed in the guest room with a comfortable queen. We also replaced the game room and guest rooms with new smart TVs. We regularly add new artwork and supplies. The property now has a caretaker on site who has created a back yard space with a garden and chickens. They share their tomatoes and eggs when they can.
transit: You need a car to discover the area but will be happy to stay on the grounds and relax by the pool, on the porches, or in the game room. A covered 2 car carport is on site. Parking is no problem. Some guests have used Ride Austin or other ride sharing from the airport. They report the cost was in the $50 range.

neighborhood_overview: Hyde Park is a quiet and relaxing neighborhood.  You will be within walking distance to some of the best local restaurants and bakeries that Austin has to offer, yet you wouldn't know it because of the quiet atmosphere.  It's common to see people running or walking their dogs at all times of the day.  There's very little traffic on the streets, which makes it a great place to walk around and look at all of the historic Victorian homes built in the late 1800's to early 1900's.  Go visit the free local museum in the neighborhood or enjoy a coffee at the local coffee shop within walking distance.
